ambridge Spies]]'' || [[Kim Philby]] ||\n|-\n| 2003 || ''[[Agatha Christie's Poirot]]'' ''Five Little Pigs'' || Philip Blake || Based on the book ''[[Five Little Pigs]]'' by [[Agatha Christie]]\n|-\n| 2004 || ''[[London (TV series)|London]]'' || [[Casanova]] ||\n|-\n| 2005|| ''[[Waking the Dead (TV series)|Waking the Dead]]'' || Dr Nick Henderson || Season 5, Episodes 5 and 6 (''Subterraneans'', Parts I and II)\n|-\n| 2005 || ''[[The Queen's Sister]]'' || [[Anthony Armstrong-Jones]] ||\n|-\n| 2006 || ''The Best Man'' || Peter Tremaine ||\n|-\n| 2006 ||''[[Secrets of the Dead]]: The Umbrella Assassin'' || Narrator || Season 5, Episode 5; an account of the murder of [[Georgi Markov]]\n|-\n| 2006 || ''[[Sharpe's Challenge]]'' || [[William Dodd (fiction)|William Dodd]] || Based on [[Bernard Cornwell]]'s [[Richard Sharpe (fictional character)|Richard Sharpe]] series\n|-\n| 2006 || ''[[Jane Eyre (2006 miniseries)|Jane Eyre]]'' || Edward Fairfax Rochester || Based on the book ''[[Jane Eyre]]'' by [[Charlotte Bront\u00eb]]\n|-\n| 2007 || ''The Wild West \u2013 Custer's Last Stand'' || General [[George Armstrong Custer]] || Dramatised documentary\n|-\n| 2008 || ''[[Wired (TV series)|Wired]]'' || Crawford Hill || Mini-Series\n|-\n| 2009 || ''[[The Best Job in the World (advertising)|The Best Job in the World]]'' || Narrator || Documentary based on [[Tourism Queensland]]'s publicity stunt for a barrier islands' 'caretaker'\n|-\n| 2009 || ''[[Robin Hood (2006 TV series)|Robin Hood]]'' || Prince [[John, King of England|John of England]] || Series 3 episodes 6\u20138\n|-\n| 2010 || ''[[Strike Back (TV series)|Strike Back]]'' || Arlington || Based on the book by [[Chris Ryan]]\n|-\n| 2010 || ''Lost: The Mystery of Flight 447'' || Narrator ||  Documentary on [[Air France Flight 447]]\n|-\n| 2010 || ''[[Agatha Christie's Marple]]'' ''The Blue Geranium'' || George Pritchard || A [[Miss Marple]] mystery based on the [[Agatha Christie]] short story (first published in [[The Thirteen Pr