); play by [[Shakespeare]]<br> Stephens won the [[Ian Charleson Award]] and the Sir John Gielgud Award\n|-\n| 1994 || ''[[A Midsummer Night's Dream]]'' || Lysander|| Directed by [[Adrian Noble]] (RSC); play by [[Shakespeare]]\n|-\n| 1994 || ''[[Measure for Measure]]'' || Claudio || Directed by [[Steven Pimlott]] (RSC); play by [[Shakespeare]]\n|-\n| 1996 || ''[[A Streetcar Named Desire (play)|A Streetcar Named Desire]]'' || [[Stanley Kowalski]] || Directed by Sir [[Peter Hall (theatre director)|Peter Hall]] (The Haymarket); play by [[Tennessee Williams]]\n|-\n| 1998/99 || ''[[Phedre]]'' || Hippolytus || Directed by [[Jonathan Kent (director)|Jonathan Kent]] (Almeida & Brooklyn Academy); play by [[Jean Racine]]\n|-\n| 1998/99 || ''[[Britannicus (play)|Britannicus]]'' || [[Nero]] || Directed by [[Jonathan Kent (director)|Jonathan Kent]] (Almeida & Brooklyn Academy); play by [[Jean Racine]]\n|-\n| 1999 || ''Ring Round the Moon'' || Hugo/Frederick|| Directed by Gerry Gutierrez ([[Lincoln Center Theater]] NY); play by [[Jean Anouilh]]<br> Stephens' Broadway debut; he received the Theatre World Award\n|-\n| 2001 || ''Japes'' || Japes || Directed by Sir [[Peter Hall (theatre director)|Peter Hall]] (The Haymarket); play by [[Simon Gray]]\n|-\n| 2001 || ''[[The Royal Family (play)|The Royal Family]]'' || Anthony Cavendish || Directed by Sir [[Peter Hall (theatre director)|Peter Hall]] (The Haymarket); play by [[George S. Kaufman]] and [[Edna Ferber]]\n|-\n| 2004 || ''[[Hamlet]]'' || [[Prince Hamlet|Hamlet]]|| Directed by [[Michael Boyd (director)|Michael Boyd]] (RSC); play by [[Shakespeare]]\n|-\n| 2004 || ''The Pilate Workshop'' || Jesus || Directed by [[Michael Boyd (director)|Michael Boyd]] (RSC); play by [[Helen Edmundson]], based on Ann Wroe's [[Pontius Pilate]]: The Biography of an Invented Man\n|-\n| 2007 || ''[[Betrayal (play)|Betrayal]]'' || Jerry || Directed by [[Roger Michell]] (Donmar); play by [[Harold Pinter]]\n|-\n| 2007 || ''[[The Country Wife]]'' || Mr. Horn